e?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 2:03:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> FFA Questions</span><hr size=1> Who decides?<br>
<br>
When Vazaelle opened up in December 2000, how was it determined that it would be a FFA server?  What are the other options?  Can a server change from FFA to some other form of &quot;government&quot;?  If so, how?<br>
<br>
-&gt; Durok<br>
<br>
P.S.  This is not a petition or request to change....I just am curious. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saalron>Saalron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 373<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 2:27:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> defaults</span><hr size=1> There's nothing on Verant's side that has Vazaelle posted as a FFA community, it's not something official or patrolled.<br>
<br>
Basically, the first few guilds capable of removing content that doesn't respawn within a reasonable timeframe will wind up setting the pace. This will condition up-and-coming guilds to get better at playing the game that is laid out before them and tilt them towards keeping that trend going.<br>
<br>
Changing a whole server of people's opinions is not an easy thing to do. Humanity, like most chunks of physics, tend to lean towards the situation requiring the least amount of energy. I know that personally, I have no desire to find out when someone has something 'reserved', if the thing I wanna beat up is dead, I'll go find something else to beat up, and then some other time come back to find my original target. To move the whole server from FFA to 'governed' you'd need to create a paradigm shift for all of the forces that can raid the content in question AND make sure that as new people were to start to join into the mix of people pursuing raid mobs that they also would want to adhere to your government.<br>
<br>
In real life, you've got things like money and brute force to install a government. In EQ you've basically got nothing but politics and there are a lot of people who would spite you for even trying, so best of luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udurokh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 2:43:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: defaults</span><hr size=1> Thanks Saalron -<br>
<br>
As I mentioned, I am not interested in changing Vazaelle's status, just curious as to how it got there.  This curiosity was prompted by a post on another messaage thread proposing that the server status be changed from FFA.<br>
<br>
Anyway, your answer was what I suspected the situation to be.  Thanks again.<br>
<br>
-&gt; Durok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usotae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sotae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 453<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 2:48:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: defaults</span><hr size=1> i think it was something like this... we had a calender up, that people could use, mainly for just courtesy.... 2 guilds decided it was time to kill vox/nagafen at the same time... promethian order, and sacred fires....  PO put up a nag raid on the calender, we honored it, let them kill him first.... then the next week, po put up a vox raid on the calender, there was a newly scheduled patch, so before the patch, we decided to try on vox... the guild leader of po and i talked a bit, i told him that we weren't jumping their raid on her, since there was a patch, and that we were going to do nag the next day, they wanted to do nag the next day... well we got there first and killed him, and thus, the start of FFA...<br>
<br>
check the archives and the &quot;i don't usually rant...&quot; thread, it was right after that happened <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udurokh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 3:09:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: defaults</span><hr size=1> Ugh.  I read several mind-numbing pages of that thread and had enough.  Did a meeting of the dominant guild leaders ever take place?<br>
<br>
-&gt; Durok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saalron>Saalron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 374<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 3:10:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> np</span><hr size=1> All good, Durok. A lot of people assume there's something in place for how the higher end game of EQ works.<br>
<br>
But the truth is that there is absolutely nothing in place at all until someone decides to do something, then does it. Have fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 537<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 3:35:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: np</span><hr size=1> EverQuest is FFA by nature.  Verant and its GM's will not respect a calendar.  For a calendar to work, all raid guilds must respect it.<br>
<br>
Calendars were a lot more useful during the pre-expansion days when there was a limited amount of raid content in EQ.  It may have been more reasonable to request that people share what little there was.<br>
<br>
Now that there's so much raid content in EQ, there's little reason that guilds should need to reserve mobs in order to have something to do.<br>
<br>
Blue EQ servers may be Player vs Environment, however raid-level EQ is still a very competitive.  The rewards are there for those dedicated enough to take them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udurokh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 4:12:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: np</span><hr size=1> Anyone know of a server that is not FFA?  In practice as well as in theory, that is.<br>
<br>
-&gt; Durok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utenkenofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenken of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/02 6:42:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2286.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.hawaii.rr.com/kcsystems/ten/domo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: np</span><hr size=1> FFA, or FCFS is the most efficient policy to follow. At the time, it didn't really matter as much because I doubt any clerics were waiting for Naggy's death to clear the way for Ragefire. But when clerics began lining up to get old Ragey, you wanted him dead, dead, dead, as fast as possible. If you were lucky you could have a couple of chances at him. Also, you wanted him dead as quickly as possible to maximize the possibilities of him dropping loot like, scales, cloaks and stuff. Assuming no patches and server crashes, that would mean roughly 52 spawns a year, one per week. Luckily (or unluckily, depending on your opinion), after every server reset (patch, maintenance, crash, etc.) we have a brand new Naggy (and Vox).<br>
<br>
Now, Naggy and that white witch are mostly for lower guilds to get their early raiding experience. Or for a guild's twinks to go farm shiznit. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just apply the above theory to all other big mobs that come later in the game and you have what we have now.<br>
